wiki.summary: Much like the majority of the project, “Lost & Found Freestyle 2019” was first previewed at Nigo’s debut collection for Kenzo’s Autumn/Winter 2022 collection in Paris on January 23, 2022. After the sneak listen of Tyler, The Creator’s verse on the track, Steven Victor, the executive producer of I Know NIGO!, revealed A$AP Rocky was also on the record, claiming Rocky put the track together. “Lost & Found Freestyle 2019” would be the first collaboration from the WANG$AP duo since Lil Yachty’s 2020 hit album cut, “T.D.” Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: Much like the majority of the project, “Lost & Found Freestyle 2019” was first previewed at Nigo’s debut collection for Kenzo’s Autumn/Winter 2022 collection in Paris on January 23, 2022. After the sneak listen of Tyler, The Creator’s verse on the track, Steven Victor, the executive producer of I Know NIGO!, revealed A$AP Rocky was also on the record, claiming Rocky put the track together. “Lost & Found Freestyle 2019” would be the first collaboration from the WANG$AP duo since Lil Yachty’s 2020 hit album cut, “T.D.” The instrumental, produced by Pharrell Williams and Chad Hugo under the Neptunes name, extensively samples and reworks Houston rapper Slim Thug’s “3 Kings" and “Like A Boss,” both from his 2005 album Already Platinum.
